==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|it}} {{term||lang=it|banca rotta}}, which refers to an out-of-business bank, having its bench physically broken. When a moneylender in Northern Italy would become insolvent, they would break the bench they worked from to signify that they were no longer in business.

